<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="588" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/1524: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                            Chungking</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-10T17:00:00-04:00">August 10, 1938—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>227. Your 400, August 7, noon, in regard to automobile and bicycle
                            license fees at Chefoo. The Department concurs in the opinion of the
                            Embassy that the license fees in question do not appear to be
                            unreasonable and that, provided the fees are collected from foreigners
                            and Chinese without discrimination and the funds so collected are used
                            for road repairs, American nationals should be advised to pay the fees
                            as voluntary contributions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
